      },
      "lineNbr": 353,
      "author": {
        "id": 5631
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-10T19:55:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sorry - yeah. Scalar architecture being one where the actual ALUs in the GPU are actually scalar (rather than 4-wide SIMD). Despite GPU shading languages looking very SIMD-like, to my knowledge every architecture is actually scalar these days (and has been for a while). It just makes scheduling much easier (and eliminates huge inefficiencies when only some of the four lanes are being used in any given calculation).\n\nSo read that as: \"Yes, on any relatively modern GPU, it will produce the same code\".",
      "parentUuid": "7fb06116_e4ac88bd",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 353,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 353,
        "endChar": 67
